</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Soldiers yesterday killed a Palestinian in the occupied West Bank after he
refused to produce his identity card, the army said, AP writes from
Jerusalem. It was the second successive day troops have killed a Palestinian
in the West Bank. The shooting happened in the village of Salfit where
troops asked a Palestinian to show his identity card, said an army official,
speaking on condition of anonymity.
