<HEADLINE>
FT  09 JAN 92 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Christmas was a dull and featureless period for the wool market. However,
with the US dollar weaker as a result of an interest rate reduction, and
sterling weaker within Europe as a result of interest rate rises there,
individual re-calculation of prices has often been necessary. Non-payment of
debts by successors of the Soviet Union is a disturbing feature in assessing
prospects in the second half of the Australian selling season, which opens
next week. South African wool prices at a sale on January 8 were around 7%
lower and there was a poor clearance to the trade, which cannot be seen as a
good omen.
</TEXT>
