The owner, Mr Hubert Burda, traditionally ploughs back all profits -
expected to be DM75m in 1991 - into new plant and publications.
In the past year, it has bombarded easterners with a range of lurid
full-colour newspapers and magazines such as Super-Zeitung, which now sells
450,000 a day, matching the east German circulation of the long-established
Bild.
Burda opened a new print works in Berlin in a joint venture with News
International.
