<HEADLINE>
FT  08 JAN 92 / Observer: Menage a deux
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
There is an engaging family overtone to the European Bank for Reconstruction
and Development's first big east-west investment, a Dollars 20m stake in a
consortium to buy 40 per cent of CSA, the Czechoslovak state airline. The
consortium is headed by Air France, which is putting up only Dollars 6m in
cash. Air France is run by Bernard Attali. The EBRD is run by Jacques
Attali, his twin brother. But I am promised it was an entirely arm's length
arrangement.
</TEXT>
