FT  08 JAN 92 / Commodities and Agriculture: Pakistan cotton crop up sharply
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   KARACHI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
PAKISTAN'S cotton production totalled 8.2m bales (each of 375 lb) between
the start of the 1991-92 season in September and January 1, up from 7m bales
in the corresponding period of 1990, reports Reuter from Karachi.
The 1991-92 harvest, which will run till April, was likely to reach 11m
bales, up from the 1990-91 record of 9.7m, said Mr Khwaja Mohammad Ilyas,
acting chairman of the Pakistan Cotton Ginners' Association. He said the
state-run Cotton Export Corporation of Pakistan had purchased 741,021 bales,
up from last year's 22,600 bales.
