FT  08 JAN 92 / Deficit forecast at Bell Atlantic
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BELL ATLANTIC, the US telecoms group, expects to post a 1991 year-end loss.
It blames the loss on a Dollars 1.55bn accounting change charge that will be
retroactive to the first 1991 quarter, Reuter reports.
The company, which plans to restate results for the first three quarters of
1991, said the charge related to its adoption of Financial Accounting
Standard Number 106, which affects its accounting of retiree health and life
insurance benefits.
In 1990, Bell Atlantic earned Dollars 1.31bn, or Dollars 3.38 a share, on
revenues of Dollars 12.30bn.
Excluding the charge, the company said its earnings from operations were on
track to meet analysts' expectations.
