<HEADLINE>
FT  07 JAN 92 / International Company News: Du Pont faces Dollars 3bn-plus
charge to meet standard
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
DU PONT, the US chemicals group, expects to take a Dollars 3bn to Dollars
4bn one-time after-tax charge against earnings in the first quarter of 1993
to comply with a new standard of accounting for the post-retirement health
benefits of employees.
All US companies have to adopt the new standard by 1993. Many big
corporations have announced similarly large non-cash charges against
earnings. The standard allows the charge to be taken in one blow, as Du Pont
proposes, or amortised over 20 years.
