</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Low sales and a lack of business is the most important problem facing small
businesses, according to the latest NatWest Quarterly Survey of Small
Business.*
Forty per cent of small businesses identified this issue, the largest
proportion ever to agree on a single concern, and an indication of the depth
of the recession, NatWest said.
