<HEADLINE>
FT  07 JAN 92 / Management (The Growing Business): The right time to go it
alone - In a Nutshell
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Only 4 per cent of small business owners would advise others thinking of
starting a firm not to do so, according to research carried out for National
Westminster Bank.
The most popular advice from the more than 800 small businesses up to two
years old which were polled was: check carefully, do your homework and get
expert advice. Eight per cent of those questioned advised against starting
up with too little capital.
Asked for the biggest hurdle they had to jump, one in five small business
owners cited sustaining and monitoring cash flow while one in six reported
it had been finding the original finance.
